							<p>During times of emergency, people often debate whether it&#39;s safer to stay in the countryside or in an urban area. However, the answer to this question depends on the nature of the crisis. If there is a pandemic outbreak, residing in a farm in the countryside away from people in the city may be safer. But, if there is a serious food shortage in the city and society has collapsed, farms may become unsafe.</span></p>

							<p>The reason behind the farms becoming unsafe during a food shortage is because everyone knows that food is grown on farms, and that&#39;s where people will head to get food. In any crisis, the places with a higher population density, such as cities and suburban areas, will become more dangerous. This is because people are unpredictable, and you never know who might resort to desperate measures to get what they want.</span></p>

							<p>Despite the risks, urban areas are where many people live and work. Therefore, it&#39;s crucial to have urban survival strategies in place during times of emergency. In this article, we&#39;ll take a look at a few strategies to prevent you from becoming another statistic to the common crimes that take place during emergencies. By being aware of these strategies, you can increase your chances of survival in an urban area during a crisis.</span></p>

							<p><strong>ENSURING HOME SECURITY</strong></span></p>

							<p>Ensuring the safety of your home should be a top priority for any prepper. It&#39;s advisable to seek the services of a professional security consultant to conduct an assessment of your home and provide recommendations on how to enhance your home security. It&#39;s not recommended to attempt to secure your home on your own since most people lack experience in this area, and criminals can be very resourceful.</p>

							<p>To start with, your doors should be sturdy and reinforced. Installing CCTV cameras at different entrances, exits, and blind spots can provide valuable surveillance footage. Motion sensor floodlights that activate when someone is lurking around at night can also be an effective deterrent for criminals. Additionally, a well-trained guard dog can be an excellent addition to your security setup.</p>

							<p>It&#39;s important to note that hiding spare keys outside your home should be avoided at all costs. Criminals are aware of common hiding places and can easily gain access to your home. By taking the necessary precautions and implementing these security measures, you can ensure that your home remains safe and secure.</p>

							<p> <strong>DEALING WITH STALKERS</strong> </p>

							<p>During disasters like earthquakes or hurricanes, people tend to stay at home and only venture out for essential errands like grocery shopping or visiting hospitals. However, the quietness outside during these times can make people vulnerable to being stalked by criminals looking for an opportunity to strike.</p>

							<p>If you notice someone following or stalking you, it is important not to panic and speed up your pace as this may alert them to your suspicions and cause them to take immediate action to overpower you. Instead, try to walk into a nearby store and ask the staff to call the police. This will help deter the stalker from attacking you and allow the authorities to intervene before any harm is done.</p>

							<p>If there are no stores around, it is essential to be prepared for self-defense. Keep a weapon like pepper spray or a personal alarm in your handbag or pocket and have it ready to use in case of an emergency. It is also important to maintain your composure and not give away that you are aware of being stalked. This will give you the element of surprise if the stalker decides to attack, increasing your chances of defending yourself and staying safe.</p>

							<p> <strong> REMOTE AREAS </strong> </p>

							<p>It is best to minimize your presence in isolated areas as much as possible to reduce the risk of being a target for criminals. Parking lots that have poor lighting or are located in basements can be prime locations for criminals to commit crimes. Even taking a shortcut through a lonely park could be risky if someone is aware of your daily routine. Therefore, it is advisable to avoid these areas and choose well-lit and well-populated routes instead.</span></p>

							<p> <strong> FIREARMS </strong></p>

							<p>Using firearms for self-protection can be one of the best forms of defense, but it can also be the most dangerous. It&#39;s crucial to know how to use them well. When storing firearms at home, it&#39;s important that they&#39;re easily accessible to you, but not to your kids. You should always keep them unloaded.</p>

							<p>If you hear noises in your home in the middle of the night, you should always shout at the intruder and ask them to identify themselves before using your firearm to protect yourself. Firing blindly in the dark could be disastrous. It&#39;s important to avoid accidental shootings that could occur because of panic or being too quick to use your firearm. It&#39;s best to get proper training to know how to handle firearms safely and effectively.</p>

							<p> <strong> AUTOMOBILES </strong></p>

							<p>To ensure your safety during a crisis, it is crucial to have a well-maintained vehicle with sufficient fuel. You never know when you may need to make a quick trip or evacuate. Transportation is essential during times of emergency. However, it is also important to be cautious and vigilant about your safety while using your vehicle. There is always a risk of car-jacking or kidnapping if you are not careful.</p>

							<p>It is recommended to keep your doors locked and windows rolled up while waiting at stoplights. This is particularly important for women who may be more vulnerable to such situations. It is best to avoid entertaining strangers who try to engage you when you are out late at night. If you feel unsafe, be prepared to hit the gas and make a quick escape.</p>

							<p>It is essential to keep these safety tips in mind at all times. During desperate times, people may resort to desperate measures, and there is no telling what a stranger might do if they have ill-intent. It is not paranoia but a survival instinct to stay alert and prepared for any unexpected situations.<br />
							&nbsp;</p>

