							<p><strong>Bartering Mindlessly</strong></p>

							<p>When we think of bartering, we usually think of exchanging goods, but that&#39;s not the only thing you can trade. In a post-disaster situation, you&#39;re likely to have acquired a number of useful skills for your own survival. These skills can also be marketable. Sometimes, the person with the right skills is more valuable to the community than the person with something to sell. If you have the ability to make or do things that will help others survive, they may see you as someone to protect rather than someone to rob.</p>

							<p>In a post-disaster world, your survival skills could be as valuable as the physical goods you stockpile. Here are some examples of skills that could be in demand:</p>

							<ul>
								<li style="list-style-type:disc">Blacksmithing: the art of forging and shaping metal objects</li>
