				<!-- 4. Ensuring Safety While Searching for a New Shelter Section-->
				<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tab4" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="nav-4-tab">
					<div class="row">	
						<div class="col-12">
							<!-- Section Heading-->
							<h2 class="sub-header-salesperson text-center">
								<span  class="text-danger"> <strong>Ensuring Safety While Searching for a New Shelter</strong> </span>							
							</h2>
							<!-- Icon Divider-->
							<div class="divider-custom">
								<div class="divider-custom-line"></div>
								<div class="divider-custom-icon"><i class="fas fa-star"></i></div>
								<div class="divider-custom-line"></div>
							</div>
							<!-- Section Content-->
							<p>>Imagine your home has been destroyed due to a flood, and you&#39;re left with nothing but your bug-out bag. Alternatively, a terrorist attack may occur near your location, making the area dangerous, and you need to evacuate to a safer place. In both cases, finding a new shelter becomes essential. However, the question arises: where do you go?</p>

							<p>>For many individuals, staying with friends or family could be an option. But if that&#39;s not feasible, finding a motel or hotel to stay in becomes a necessity. The situation becomes even more complex if you&#39;re abroad and need to locate a safe place during an emergency.</p>

							<p>>Selecting the wrong shelter could be more dangerous than staying where you are. A news story in the past mentioned a British tourist who jumped out of her hotel balcony in India to escape from a man who was harassing her.</p>

							<p>>This experience highlights the importance of being cautious and thoughtful when deciding on a place to stay. This article provides a few essential tips that can guide you in making a sound decision that not only ensures the safety of your belongings but could also save your life.</p>

							<p><strong>What The Area Should Be Like</strong></p>

							<p>>To ensure your safety, it&#39;s crucial to select a motel or hotel in an area that&#39;s relatively safe. Opting for a place located in a dangerous area that is notorious for crime, vagrancy, and other such unsavory activities could potentially put you in harm&#39;s way. Being in such an environment would increase the likelihood of you being accosted outside the hotel, and even your room might not be secure due to the presence of criminals lurking around.</p>

							<p><strong>Security Is Priority</strong></p>

							<p>>It&#39;s important to confirm whether your hotel or motel has security measures in place. However, it&#39;s crucial to keep in mind that this alone may not guarantee safety, particularly in countries where security personnel can be bribed. Additionally, it&#39;s advisable to check if security personnel are present at night, if CCTV cameras are installed to discourage criminals, and if the area is well-lit. These factors play a significant role in determining the safety of the location.</p>

							<p><strong>Ground Floor Is Not A Choice</strong></p>

							<p>>Opt for a hotel room on higher floors whenever possible. Choosing a motel room on the ground floor can make it easier for criminals to break in and rob or harm you.</p>

							<p><strong>Your Social Environment</strong></p>

							<p>>It&#39;s important to consider the type of guests that the hotel or motel attracts. While it&#39;s easy to assume that external threats are the only dangers, it&#39;s important to remember that sometimes the enemy can be within. Staying in a budget motel that attracts unsavory characters could put you at risk of theft or other crimes. On the other hand, staying in a high-end establishment where prominent people stay could make the place a potential target in the event of a terrorist attack.</p>

							<p><strong>Additional Tips</strong></p>

							<p>>In addition to the aforementioned points, it is crucial to exercise common sense when staying in an unfamiliar place. Refrain from giving out personal information, such as your room number, to strangers.</p>

							<p>>Familiarize yourself with all emergency exits in the building and know precisely where to go in case you need to make a swift escape. It is also advisable to locate the closest hospital and police station.</p>

							<p>>By following the tips provided above, you can ensure your safety. During a crisis, it is easy to become overwhelmed and make hasty decisions. However, it is essential to remain calm and make the right choices to guarantee your survival. Your life depends on it.</p>
						</div>
						<a class="btn-next" href="#nav-tab" id="tab4-next">
							NEXT
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<!-- 5. Increasing Your Awareness to Stay Safe Section-->
				<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tab5" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="nav-5-tab">
					<div class="row">
						<div class="col-12">
							<!-- Section Heading-->
							<h2 class="sub-header-salesperson text-center">
								<span  class="text-danger"> <strong>Increasing Your Awareness to Stay Safe</strong> </span>
							</h2>
							<!-- Icon Divider-->
							<div class="divider-custom">
								<div class="divider-custom-line"></div>
								<div class="divider-custom-icon"><i class="fas fa-star"></i></div>
								<div class="divider-custom-line"></div>
							</div>
							<!-- Section Content-->
							<p>In times of emergency, your level of control over the situation is directly linked to your level of proactivity. Reactive individuals tend to have lower awareness levels and can be taken by surprise when sudden acts of violence occur. Unfortunately, many people have fallen victim to crimes such as theft, rape, robbery, and murder simply because they were unaware of their surroundings. As a prepper, it&#39;s important to remember that if you&#39;re not actively looking for potential threats, you&#39;re unlikely to spot them before it&#39;s too late.</p>

							<p><strong>Remain Vigilant for Suspicious Activity</strong></p>

							<p>To increase your situational awareness, it&#39;s important to be vigilant for anything that appears suspicious or unusual. In times of crisis, crime rates tend to rise, and even during periods of peace, criminals are constantly on the lookout for easy targets. While it could be anyone who falls victim, you don&#39;t want it to be you.</p>

							<p>If you observe an unknown individual repeatedly walking past your house, take note and inform the authorities instead of assuming they&#39;re harmless. Even if they&#39;re dressed like a landscaper or someone who belongs in the neighborhood, there might be something wrong. They may be assessing your property and planning a break-in later. It&#39;s always better to err on the side of caution.</p>

							<p><strong>Risk Mitigation</strong></p>

							<p>Human beings are generally not violent by nature. Most people avoid confrontation and physical altercations because they do not want to cause harm or be harmed. However, there are some individuals who derive pleasure from inflicting pain. These individuals may suffer from anger management issues or mental illness.</p>

							<p>Adopting a pacifist approach and believing in the ideology of non-violence, as advocated by Mahatma Gandhi, may not always be the best course of action. Being too passive and not taking action to protect oneself can make one vulnerable to becoming a victim.</p>

							<p>For instance, if someone cuts you off while driving on the road, it may be tempting to engage in a physical altercation with them. However, it is important to remain calm and composed in such situations. Similarly, if a group of youths taunt you in public, it is best to walk away rather than trying to confront them.</p>

							<p>When in potentially dangerous situations, such as on a late-night bus ride with an unfamiliar person who seems suspicious, it is essential to remain vigilant and observe their behavior without drawing attention to yourself. Ignoring the situation by burying your head in a magazine or focusing on your phone could put you at risk.</p>

							<p><strong>Confidence Is Important</strong></p>

							<p>Merely projecting confidence and the appearance of strength is often sufficient to deter potential attackers. A person who walks with purpose, keeping an eye on their surroundings, exudes an air of capability. Criminals are more likely to avoid such an individual because they don&#39;t seem like an easy target. On the other hand, someone who shuffles timidly, holding a newspaper, a cup of coffee, and a phone, while trying to open their car door, sends out a clear signal that they&#39;re vulnerable to muggers. It&#39;s important to act confident and alert, even if you&#39;re feeling nervous, because how you present yourself can make a significant difference.</p>

							<p><strong>Educate Your Kids</strong></p>

							<p>It&#39;s important to educate your children on the dangers of trusting strangers. For instance, if someone calls the house claiming to conduct a survey and your child answers the phone, they should avoid disclosing if no adult is present or revealing details about the whereabouts of family members. Such callers could potentially be plotting to burglarize your home. It&#39;s also crucial to monitor your children&#39;s online activity and make sure they only interact with trusted individuals on the internet, as strangers they meet online may pose significant threats to their safety.</span></span></p>

							<p><strong>Exercise Caution When Trusting Others</strong></p>

							<p>Finally, it&#39;s crucial never to be too trusting. Offering help to someone in need, such as a stranded motorist, may lead to becoming a victim of a carjacking. Even confiding in your neighbors about storing emergency supplies can put you at risk of being targeted during a crisis. It&#39;s important to be mindful of what you disclose to others as there can be severe consequences. In summary, during a crisis, remaining extra vigilant and aware of your surroundings is key. Pay attention to your gut instincts as they will guide you to safety.</p>

						</div>
						<a class="btn-next" href="#nav-tab" id="tab5-next">
							NEXT
						</a>
					</div>
