				<!-- 7. Before Building a Safe Room, Read This! Section-->
				<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tab7" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="nav-7-tab">
					<div class="row">	
						<div class="col-12">
							<!-- Section Heading-->
							<h2 class="sub-header-salesperson text-center">
								<span  class="text-danger"> <strong>Before Building a Safe Room, Read This!</strong> </span>							
							</h2>
							<!-- Icon Divider-->
							<div class="divider-custom">
								<div class="divider-custom-line"></div>
								<div class="divider-custom-icon"><i class="fas fa-star"></i></div>
								<div class="divider-custom-line"></div>
							</div>
							<!-- Section Content-->
							<p>Millions of people worldwide have realized the effectiveness and protection of a safe room, thanks to the Jodie Foster movie &quot;Safe Room&quot;. However, a safe room doesn&#39;t have to be as high-tech as the one in the movie. It just needs to be more secure than a regular room. Many preppers have bunkers and fallout shelters as alternative locations in case of a crisis that destroys or compromises their homes.</p>

							<p>Building a safe room may or may not be feasible depending on where you live. It&#39;s best to hire a professional to construct it for you. In countries with higher risk levels such as Iraq, etc., a safe room may be a necessity for both homes and offices. In fact, even offices and buildings in higher risk areas will have safe rooms for staff to take refuge in.</p>

							<p>If you&#39;re planning on building a safe room, there are a few essential tips you should be aware of.</p>

							<ol>
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>Interaction</strong></li>
							</ol>

							<p style="margin-left:48px">It&#39;s crucial for the safe room to have multiple means of communication with the outside world to ensure assistance can be sought if needed. Failure to do so could result in being trapped in the safe room, unsure of whether it&#39;s safe to exit.</p>

							<p style="margin-left:48px">To establish communication, it&#39;s recommended to have a landline telephone, a mobile phone, and a panic button linked to a security agency that specializes in emergency response. In the event of taking shelter in a safe room, external help is usually required to secure the area and make it safe.</p>

							<ol start="2">
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>Nourishment and hydration.</strong></li>
							</ol>

							<p style="margin-left:48px">Adequate provisions of nourishment and hydration must be stocked in the safe room to sustain the occupants for a few days.</p>

							<ol start="3">
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>First Aid Kit</strong></li>
							</ol>

							<p style="margin-left:48px">In the event of an injury, the first aid kit will be essential.</p>

							<ol start="4">
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>FireProof &amp; Bullet Proof Shelter</strong></li>
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>Fire Extinguishers</strong></li>
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>Sleeping Essentials</strong></li>
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>Lightings And Extra Battery</strong></li>
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>Radio</strong></li>
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>Self Defence Tools</strong></li>
								<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><strong>Toiletries</strong></li>
							</ol>

							<p>To sum up, it&#39;s crucial that the security company is aware of the location of your safe room and they may need to survey your home to create a map of the exact location. This will enhance their effectiveness during a rescue mission. In conclusion, constructing a safe room is an excellent idea, and if feasible within your space and budget, it&#39;s recommended to build one. Alternatively, you can consider building a bunker as a substitute if constructing a safe room in your own home is not feasible.</p>
						</div>
						<a class="btn-next" href="#nav-tab" id="tab7-next">
							NEXT
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<!-- 8. Crucial Tips To Help You Not Loose Your Mind In Survival Situations Section-->
				<div class="tab-pane fade" id="tab8" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="nav-8-tab">
					<div class="row">
						<div class="col-12">
							<!-- Section Heading-->
							<h2 class="sub-header-salesperson text-center">
								<span  class="text-danger"> <strong>Crucial Tips To Help You Not Loose Your Mind In Survival Situations</strong> </span>
							</h2>
							<!-- Icon Divider-->
							<div class="divider-custom">
								<div class="divider-custom-line"></div>
								<div class="divider-custom-icon"><i class="fas fa-star"></i></div>
								<div class="divider-custom-line"></div>
							</div>
							<!-- Section Content-->
							<p>Stress is a common part of life, but it can escalate quickly in times of crisis. Whether it&#39;s a natural disaster like a flood or hurricane, or being in a warzone, such traumatic events can leave you feeling on edge.</p>

							<p>When you&#39;re stressed, you may experience physical symptoms like a racing heart, upset stomach, profuse sweating, and dizziness. You may find yourself easily agitated or angered by small things, and even startle or feel scared more frequently.</p>

							<p>In addition to physical symptoms, stress can take a toll on your mental health. You may feel depressed, unable to focus or concentrate, have bad dreams, and negative thoughts that make it difficult to sleep. These are all symptoms of stress-related trauma.</p>

							<p>Fortunately, there are ways to combat stress and keep your sanity in times of crisis. In this article, we&#39;ll provide six tips that you can use to manage stress and calm yourself down. By implementing these strategies, you&#39;ll be better equipped to handle chaotic situations without becoming overwhelmed.</p>

							<p><strong>Tip #1</strong></p>

							<p><strong>Visualize. </strong>Using visualization techniques is comparable to practicing the law of attraction. Through picturing serene scenarios or achieving desired goals, you can mentally detach yourself from the challenging situation at hand. As the saying goes, &quot;It&#39;s all about mind over matter. If you don&#39;t mind, it doesn&#39;t matter.&quot; Imagine things improving, assistance arriving to alleviate your burdens, and other positive scenarios to boost your morale. Harness the power of positive visualization to maintain a positive outlook.</p>

							<p><strong>Tip #2</strong></p>

							<p><strong>Deep Breathing. </strong>
							Engaging in yoga is an excellent method for reducing stress levels. However, if you are unfamiliar with yoga, taking deep breaths is a simple and effective way to calm your mind and provide your body with oxygen. Breathe deeply, hold your breath for four counts, and then slowly exhale. Repeating this process a few times can leave you feeling refreshed and reinvigorated.</p>

							<p><strong>Tip #3</strong></p>

							<p><strong>Planning. </strong>When you&#39;re in a crisis, planning can give you a sense of control over the situation. Feeling helpless and not knowing what to do can be a major source of stress for many people. This feeling of helplessness can lead to panic and anxiety.</p>

							<p>However, by taking the time to plan your next steps and being proactive, you can regain a sense of control and reduce your stress levels. Planning is a proactive approach that can help you feel more confident in handling the situation, which in turn can help you avoid feelings of despair and hopelessness.</p>

							<p><strong>Tip#4</strong></p>

							<p><strong>Educate &amp; Talk About It. </strong>
							To ease the burden of stress, it is important to communicate with family members and anyone else who is present with you about the situation. By vocalizing your thoughts, you can release pent-up emotions and feel a sense of relief.</p>

							<p><strong>Tip #5</strong></p>

							<p><strong>Dont Forget to Excercise. </strong>
							Engaging in physical activity can be one of the best ways to alleviate stress. In times of crisis, there will likely be a lot of physical tasks to complete, so keep yourself moving and try to get as much exercise as possible. Physical activity can help keep your mind occupied, preventing it from slipping into negative thought patterns. As the saying goes, &quot;an idle mind is the devil&#39;s workshop.&quot;</p>

							<p><strong>Tip #6</strong></p>

							<p><strong>Daily Routine. </strong>
							Create and stick to a daily routine, even in the midst of chaos. The predictability of a daily routine can help to reduce stress during tumultuous times. Don&#39;t forget the usual stress management techniques that work for you, and use them when you start to feel overwhelmed. Building mental toughness means finding the strength to keep going, even when you feel like you have nothing left in the tank. Remember that in difficult times, the key is to persevere and keep moving forward.</p>
	
